35.57	Communications_in_India	Communications in India	The Republic of India possesses a diversified communications system that links all parts of the country by Internet, telephone, telegraph, radio, and television. Most of the telecommunications forms are as prevalent or as advanced as those in modern Western countries, and the system includes some of the most sophisticated technology in the world and constitutes a foundation for further development of a modern network. India has the world's second-largest mobile phone users with over 903 million as of January 2012. It has the world's third-largest Internet users with over 121 million as of December 2011. India has become the world's most competitive and one of the fastest growing telecom markets.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/BSNL_Microwave_Tower_Mangalore_0210.JPG/150px-BSNL_Microwave_Tower_Mangalore_0210.JPG
